Rating: 1
Served this at Easter. I thought it was just okay. My guests seemed to enjoy it though. After steaming I immediately put the veggies in an ice bath- it stopped them from cooking and preserved the color.

Rating: 2
It was okay - I'll make it again but include a few of my favorite veggies like beets, potatoes, & green beans. Also, I dumped all the veggies into a bowl to dress and marinate - unfortunately, the broccoli continued to steam because of the trapped heat - next time I'll use a cookie sheet so the veggies are in a single layer.

Rating: 3
Tastes delicious. The only problem I had was that the broccoli faded from bright green (after being steamed) to a less desirable color after being in the refrigerator overnight. I used 2 teaspoons dijon mustard since the recipe did not specify.

