What is the 2 Dijon-style mustard? Teaspoons or Tablespoons?

Rating: 4
I've made this twice for 2 family gatherings and each time there's not much left. In place of pearl onions, I used a red onion, thinly sliced which I added along with the peppers. I added all colors available for the bell peppers, used the smallest baby carrots. It made such a beautiful and colorful addition to the table. Next time I would like to add either sunflower seeds or slivered/sliced almonds.

Rating: 4
This is a wonderful dish that makes a colorful side and gets lots of vegetables in those who don't care much for them! It is easy to prepare and a joy to serve.

Rating: 4
Wow! This dish was so simple, but so delicious. I wouldn't change a single thing. Veggies came out perfectly cooked, not soggy at all. I'm thinking of making this again as part of our Easter dinner.